gujarati.context:
Here are the translations:

Someone does the deed, the consequences follow, one becomes steadfast in good or bad; 
The day knows time and land, I call such a saint my Shish.

Dagò nahe sangrharhita, viveki vichar dharmavanta;
Sada pavitra ne shubhaveṣha, evā santane nāmuḥ śīśa.

Becomes:

There is no sorrow without gathering, wise people think in accordance with dharma; 
Always pure one's name is good for such a saint.
